The paper introduces a new concept of Modular Autoencoder (MAE) for learning diverse but complementary representations from unlabelled data, which can later be used for supervised tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on six benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of gradient descent and SVD-based algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Computation and Language (cs.CL).
